Notifications
=============

Laravel includes a notification class which yu can use in the model file (use notifiable).

Notifications table
--------------------
Laravel comes with the structure for the notifications table. You can create a notifications table using the command 
php artisan notifications:table then php artisan migrate

Notifications file
-------------------
You can also create a notifications file using the command
php artisan make:notification <filename>

This creates a notifications folder in the app directory and a new file in this folder.

In the notifications file specify the via route (e.g. email) and specify to array (text to be inserted into the table)
